description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and motivated Speech and Language Therapist - Band 5, to join our team in the beautiful areas of Wisbech and Fenland in Cambridgeshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to promotion and maternity leave, we are searching for a first class clinician with great relationship-building skills to be part of our award winning, multidisciplinary team, helping us to change the lives of children and young people with communication difficulties across Cambridgeshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will manage a caseload providing targeted, evidence-based therapy to children and young people who have a range of speech, language and communication needs. They will be the link therapist for a number of schools in a designated area and will also see children in clinic and provide support for some children in special schools as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time position but we may consider part-time for the right applicant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If this sounds like your type of role, use the job link below, we’d love to hear from you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please email: Susie Robertson, Area &amp; Clinical Lead –Fenland and Huntingdon. Email: susie.robertson@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The Cambridgeshire and Peterborough Speech and Language Therapy Service is delivered in partnership between Cambridgeshire Community Services NHS Trust and Cambridgeshire and Peterborough NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Children and Young People’s Services: provided in partnership by Cambridgeshire&lt;em&gt;Community Services NHS Trust and Cambridgeshire and Peterborough NHS Foundation Trust&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
